<br>
Aside from that, It's quite obvious that guns are dangerous, but think about how many people's lives are saved everyday by guns in the hands of skilled and *legal* users. <br>
<br>
Are guns dangerous? YES! No doubt! If children are around, any guns should be locked, and left unloaded at all times except when in use. Even if children are not around, the clip (or the bullets since we're talking about a revolver) should be removed from the gun, altho you could leave it nearby in case you need it for protection.<br>
<br>
So is it fair to say guns are bad? No. The person wielding the gun is bad. <br>
<br>
And even if guns had never been developed, children and everyone else would still die accidentally by other means. Also, if there were no guns... consider how brutal war would be... and don't say we wouldn't have war, because that simply isn't true. War is simply part of man's nature, it has been long before guns ever came along.<br>
<br>
