<br>
Also on bullet types.  Full metal jackets on hunting ammo is very rare.  They pass through tissue without doing much damage.  All bullets are made of lead, malleable metal, which expands on impact, therefore causing damage.  There's a variety of variations with different shapes and coatings to control the expansion of the metal.  More lethal bullets are regulated differently in different states.<br>
<br>
